      • create

        public static PathlingContext create​(@Nonnull
                                     SparkSession sparkSession,
                                     @Nullable
                                     String versionString,
                                     @Nullable
                                     Integer maxNestingLevel,
                                     @Nullable
                                     Boolean enableExtensions,
                                     @Nullable
                                     List<String> enabledOpenTypes)
        Creates new instance of PathlingContext for given SparkSession, FHIR version and encoder settings. The null setting values default to the default encoders setting.
        Parameters:
        sparkSession - the SparkSession to use.
        versionString - the FHIR version to use. Must be a valid FHIR version string. If null defaults to 'R4'.
        maxNestingLevel - the maximum nesting level for recursive data types. Zero (0) indicates that all direct or indirect fields of type T in element of type T should be skipped.
        enableExtensions - switches on/off the support for FHIR extensions.
        enabledOpenTypes - list of types that are encoded within open types, such as extensions.
        Returns:
        then new instance of PathlingContext.

        @Nonnull
public Dataset<Row> encode​(@Nonnull

                           String resourceName,
                           @Nonnull
                           String inputMimeType,
                           @Nullable
                           String maybeColumnName)
        Takes a dataframe with string representations of FHIR resources and encodes the resources of the given type as a Spark dataframe.
        Parameters:
        stringResourcesDF - the dataframe with the string representation of the resources.
        resourceName - the name of the resources to encode.
        inputMimeType - the mime type of the encoding for the input strings.
        maybeColumnName - the name of the column in the input dataframe that contains the resource strings. If null the input dataframe must have a single column of type string.
        Returns:
        the dataframe with Spark encoded resources.
